# Pattern file format — kcommit-analysis-pipeline rules
# ======================================================
#
# Each *list.txt file contains one pattern per line.
# Empty lines and lines starting with # are ignored.
# Inline comments: text after whitespace + '#' is stripped  e.g. pattern  # note
#
# Pattern types (auto-detected from the line content):
#
#   keyword    Plain word or phrase, NO unescaped glob metacharacters.
#              Match is case-insensitive and whole-word (\b boundaries).
#              Examples:  overflow       use-after-free
#              Glob metacharacters can be escaped with backslash to use
#              them literally:  CVE-\*  matches the literal string "CVE-*"
#
#   glob       Pattern containing unescaped  *  ?  or  [...]  metacharacters.
#              Match is case-insensitive fnmatch against the full string.
#              Examples:  CVE-*          drivers/net/*    *.ko
#
#   re:EXPR    Regular expression prefixed with 're:'.
#              Match is case-SENSITIVE by default.
#              Use  re:(?i)EXPR  for a case-insensitive regex.
#              Examples:  re:CVE-\d{4}-\d{4,}
#                         re:(?i)buffer.overflow
#
# File naming convention:
#   keywords_whitelist.txt   — commit subject/body keyword KEEP rules
#   keywords_blacklist.txt   — commit subject/body keyword DROP rules
#   path_whitelist.txt       — touched file path KEEP rules
#   path_blacklist.txt       — touched file path DROP rules
#   commit_whitelist.txt     — SHA-based absolute KEEP rules
#   commit_blacklist.txt     — SHA-based absolute DROP rules
#
# Filter decision hierarchy (higher wins):
#   L3 commit_whitelist  > commit_blacklist  (SHA, absolute)
#   L2 path_blacklist(all files match) > path_whitelist(any file matches)
#   L2½ build_artifact coverage
#   L1½ Kconfig coverage (require_kconfig_coverage)
#   L1 keywords_whitelist > keywords_blacklist
#   L0 default: KEEP
